laboratory_examinations.findings: Dilated fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 10 mm with hyperemic wall and extensive periappendiceal fat stranding. Associated wall thickening of the base of the cecum likely reactive. No evidence of abscess formation or perforation. Multiple focal hepatic hypodensities in segment VIII, V, and VII likely represent cysts or hamartomas. Normal kidney enhancement without hydronephrosis or renal masses. Various other normal findings noted.
